---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuickSummary from '../components/QuickSummary.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="VS & Arms Race Guide"
  description="The verified VS (Alliance Duel) day-by-day table, Arms Race syncing, hoarding rules, and Saturday shield discipline."
>
  <h1>VS &amp; Arms Race</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-[#8a96b0]">The weekly optimization loop: what scores each VS day, which Arms Race phase to sync it with, and what to hoard. Last verified: July 2026.</p>

  <QuickSummary>
    <p><strong>The loop:</strong> hoard everything, spend it only on the matching VS day <em>inside</em> the matching Arms Race slot (check your in-game calendar for the exact server time) — one action, two events. Never spend during the ~5-minute dead zone after daily reset. Saturday: shield unless your alliance is actively fighting.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>The VS Day Table</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">Many blog sites publish a wrong day order (they're AI-generated and cite mechanics from other games). The day/theme/phase skeleton below is multi-source verified. Point values: lower = base, higher = with Alliance Duel research boosts.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]"><em>Note: the specific per-action point values in this table (radar tasks, stamina, speedups, shard values, promotion tiers, etc.) are community-reported and largely single-sourced, not screenshot-verified — treat the relative priorities (what to hoard, what to spend when) as reliable, and the exact numbers as pending in-game confirmation.</em></p>
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <caption class="sr-only">VS Alliance Duel daily themes, scoring actions, preparation, and matching Arms Race phase</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr><th scope="col">Day</th><th scope="col">Theme</th><th scope="col">What scores</th><th scope="col">Hoard / prepare</th><th scope="col">Arms Race sync</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><th scope="row">Mon</th><td>Radar Training</td><td>Radar tasks (~10–25K each); stamina spent (~300/pt); drone combat data &amp; parts; map gathers (score when troops <em>leave</em> the tile); drone chip chests</td><td>Stack completed-but-unclaimed radar tasks Sunday; start long gathers Sunday night; save stamina + drone data</td><td>Drone Boost</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Tue</th><td>Base Expansion</td><td>Construction speedups (~50–120/min); building power (scores when you unwrap the gift box); <strong>UR trade trucks (~100–200K each)</strong>; Legendary Secret Tasks (~75–150K); survivor recruits</td><td>Gift-wrap finished buildings Monday night; bank construction speedups + secret-order refreshes</td><td>Base Building</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Wed</th><td>Age of Science</td><td>Research speedups; tech power (claim completed research today); <strong>Valor Badges spent (~300–600 each)</strong>; Drone Component Chests; radar scores again</td><td>Time long research to finish Wed; save ALL component chests; spend Valor Badges on Duel research today — the spend itself scores</td><td>Tech Research</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Thu</th><td>Train Heroes</td><td>Hero shards (Legendary ~10–20K, epic ~3.5–7K); EW shards (~10–20K); skill medals; hero EXP; recruit tickets</td><td>Save every hero resource all week — EXP, shards, medals, tickets. Resist mid-week level-ups</td><td>Hero Advancement</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Fri</th><td>Total Mobilization</td><td><em>Everything</em>: all speedup types, building/tech power, radar, and troops by <em>arrival</em> tier (T10 ~110–258 each)</td><td>The waterfall: pre-train cheap low tiers Thursday, then promote T5→6→7→8 today — each step scores again. Hold a gift-wrapped building + remaining speedups</td><td>Unit Progression</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Sat</th><td>Enemy Buster</td><td>Rival-alliance kills (~5× value of normal kills); own losses (~6–20/unit); healing speedups; UR trucks &amp; Legendary tasks score again</td><td>Shields, hospital capacity, healing speedups. See shield discipline below</td><td>— (combat isn't an AR phase)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>How the Week Is Scored</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>Daily winner earns Victory Points: <strong>Mon 1, Tue–Fri 2 each, Sat 4</strong> (13 total — first to 7 wins, so sweeping Mon–Thu locks the week before Friday).</li>
    <li>Personal chests at 9 point tiers (40K up to 7.2M/day); tiers 4–9 require a specific research to unlock [VERIFY: exact research name unconfirmed]. Realistic mid-game floor: chest 3–4 daily.</li>
    <li><strong>Dead zone:</strong> no points during the ~5-minute countdown after daily reset. Check the event page shows the new day before spending anything.</li>
    <li><strong>Alliance Duel research is the biggest mid-game lever</strong> — per theriagames, it boosts your VS points by up to +150% at max, not a flat doubling [VERIFY: exact research name unconfirmed]. Fund it with Valor Badges from VS chests, and spend them on Wednesdays.</li>
    <li>Infinite Roulette (bonus spins past the 7.2M daily cap): per cpt-hedge, this is a limited test rollout on specific server IDs, not a general newer-server feature — check whether your server has it, and it's irrelevant until you routinely max the last chest anyway.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Arms Race Mechanics</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>Six 4-hour slots per day cycling five phases (one repeats): Base Building, Unit Progression, Tech Research, Drone Boost, Hero Advancement.</li>
    <li>Per cpt-hedge's Arms Race schedule-change guide, a past update moved toward a schedule that repeats weekly rather than shifting daily. Treat any specific server-time anchor (e.g. 08:00/20:00) as something to verify in your own in-game calendar rather than assumed — don't rely on this page for exact slot times.</li>
    <li>Each phase has 3 chests granting 1/2/3 badges (6 per phase, 36/day max). Daily Goal Chests open at <strong>2 / 8 / 18 badges</strong> — fully clearing just 3 phases hits the gold chest.</li>
    <li><strong>Slot Swap</strong> (once/day): trade the current slot with any <em>later</em> slot to pull the phase you need into your play window. You restart the swapped-in phase at 0; no extra rewards beyond the normal 36-badge cap.</li>
    <li>You're ranked against ~12–15 commanders in your HQ bracket. Point requirements jump with HQ level — don't rush an HQ level right before a big spending day.</li>
    <li>Free phase tracker: <a href="https://lastwarnexus.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">lastwarnexus.net</a>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Saturday Shield Discipline</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Default = shielded all day.</strong> Rivals can teleport to unshielded bases straight from the event UI. At HQ 15–30 you are exactly the easy-points target.</li>
    <li><strong>War Fever:</strong> per theriagames, scouting or attacking an enemy base doesn't pop an already-active shield — it blocks activating a <em>new</em> shield for ~15 minutes (and grants +1% damage). Practical takeaway is the same: don't scout or attack while unshielded on Saturday.</li>
    <li>Remove wall/drill-ground defenders Friday night — drill-ground troops count as attacker kills even with no defense set. An empty base gives the enemy almost nothing.</li>
    <li>Shield your farm accounts too; feeding the enemy gets people kicked from serious alliances.</li>
    <li>If you do fight: scout first (troopless bases give ~no points), join rallies rather than solo, and keep hospital space + healing speedups ready — your losses score points too, so controlled end-of-day trading can top up a chest.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Other Alliance Events (Quick Notes)</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Desert Storm</strong> (weekly task-force battle, per lastwartutorial.com: up to 60 per side — 20 starters + 10 subs per squad, not a flat 20v20): no permanent troop losses; split roles (frontline/backcap/harass) instead of mobbing one building; key structures unlock at 10 minutes [VERIFY]. Pays Honor Points, reportedly used toward Legendary Gear Blueprints [VERIFY].</li>
    <li><strong>Zombie Siege</strong> (20 waves): an alliance-depth problem, not a personal-power one; reinforce teammates after wave 11.</li>
    <li><strong>Zombie Invasion</strong> (biweekly): spend stamina here; Courage Medals → stamina and EW fragments in the trade store.</li>
    <li>Full per-event pages are on the roadmap — see the <a href="/stores" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">store guides</a> for what to buy with each event currency.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-[#8a96b0]">Sources: lastwartutorial.com (screenshot-verified, dev-corroborated), cpt-hedge.com (Arms Race schedule-change and Infinite Roulette coverage), lastwarvault.com, medievalfun.com, theriagames.com, official @lastwarsurvival posts. The competing day order on several blog sites was rejected as AI-generated (it cites mechanics from other games). The day names, phase names, weekly Victory Point totals, and Zombie Siege basics are cross-checked across multiple independent sources. The per-action point values in the VS day table (radar tasks, stamina, speedups, shard values, promotion tiers, and similar) are community-reported and mostly single-sourced — treat them as approximate and pending in-game verification, not screenshot-confirmed.</p>
</Layout>
